### AI Workflow Automation Platform — End-to-End Test Flow
### Use with the VS Code "REST Client" extension, or copy curl-equivalent commands.
### Run `docker compose up --build` first, then execute requests top to bottom.

@workflowService = http://localhost:5001
@triggerService = http://localhost:5002
@executionService = http://localhost:5003

### 1. Log in (dev-only endpoint, accepts any non-empty credentials) and grab the token
POST {{workflowService}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "demo-user",
  "password": "anything"
}

### 2. Create a workflow: Manual Trigger -> AI Summarize -> Email Notification
### Replace {{token}} with the token from step 1's response.
POST {{workflowService}}/api/workflows
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "name": "Summarize and Notify",
  "description": "Summarizes input text with AI, then emails the result",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "id": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
      "name": "Trigger",
      "type": "trigger",
      "configJson": "{}",
      "order": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002",
      "name": "Summarize Text",
      "type": "ai",
      "configJson": "{\"taskType\":\"summarize\",\"prompt\":\"Summarize the following text in 2 sentences.\"}",
      "order": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000003",
      "name": "Email Result",
      "type": "notification",
      "configJson": "{\"channel\":\"Email\",\"target\":\"someone@example.com\",\"subject\":\"Your summary is ready\",\"body\":\"See attached summary.\"}",
      "order": 2
    }
  ],
  "connections": [
    {
      "fromNodeId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
      "toNodeId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002"
    },
    {
      "fromNodeId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002",
      "toNodeId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000003"
    }
  ]
}

### 3. Activate the workflow (use the "id" from step 2's response)
POST {{workflowService}}/api/workflows/{{workflowId}}/activate?active=true
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 4. Create a manual trigger for the workflow
POST {{triggerService}}/api/triggers
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "workflowId": "{{workflowId}}",
  "type": 0,
  "configJson": "{}"
}

### 5. Fire the trigger (use the "id" from step 4's response as {{triggerId}})
POST {{triggerService}}/api/triggers/{{triggerId}}/fire
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "payloadJson": "{\"text\":\"Long article text to summarize goes here...\"}"
}

### 6. Check run status (use the "runId" from step 5's response)
GET {{executionService}}/api/runs/{{runId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 7. List all runs for the workflow
GET {{executionService}}/api/runs?workflowId={{workflowId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
